Introduction
============

This project is just here to test code review and code publication workflow for zena.


Init
====

1. create repository in zena
2. upload (had to add my name to sandbox users so I could use my ssh key)


Developer
=========

1. login on github (John)
2. fork sandbox
3. on local machine, clone your own fork
4. edit
5. commit
6. push ====> John's fork


Pull
====

1. To pull john/master:

# git remote add john git://github.com/john/sandbox.git
# git checkout -b john/master
# git pull john master

Now we have a branch with merged content from current master and current john/master.

2. Review code

3. Rebase

# git rebase master

3. Test

4. Merge into master

# git co master
# git merge john/master

5. Push changes to github

# git push

